Source:  Journal of the Polynesian Society
Author:
Vol / Page:  55/147
Edition:
Quote:  <i>tuna</i>, a fish (Anguilla sp.), eel, of which there are only two species in Newzealand, though there are about 110 supposed varieties named by the Maori, and even Pakehas think there are several varieties going by size, shape, and colour, but these variations are due to age and sex.
Notes:  Andersen Maori Words in English

